java.io.Serializable, Function<T,java.util.List<? extends T>>
public class MultiPrint<T>
extends AbstractFunction<T,java.util.List<? extends T>>

The MultiPrint-Function prints arguments to a specified print stream and returns them. If no print stream is specified, the standard out is taken as default. Multiple arguments will be separated by a given delimiter. Print-Functions can be used to log a composition of functions at a specified level. To do so just a Print-Function has to be inserted at the right place like 

   Function<Number, Double> sum = Functions.compose(Functions.composeMulti(Functions.div(), print), Functions.sin(), Functions.cos());
instead of 
   Function<Number, Double> tan = Functions.compose(div, sin, cos);
